Adds_Durzurgir_Status_Paralysis_Desc: Deadened nerves are sometimes preventing the execution of actions.
Adds_Kirlirger The Abhorrent_Status_Hono: Taking an honorable battle stance that will affect the next attack.
Adds_Nechuciho_Status_Forward Omen_Desc: The next attack will be executed from the front.
Adds_Nechuciho_Status_Leftward Omen_Desc: The next attack will be executed from the left.
Adds_Nechuciho_Status_Rearward Omen_Desc: The next attack will be executed from the rear.
Adds_Nechuciho_Status_Rightward Omen_Des: The next attack will be executed from the right.
Adds_Queen Hawk_Status_Bee Be Gone_Desc: Unbridled rage is increasing damage dealt. Standing too close will provoke an attack.
Adds_Queen Hawk_Status_Bee Be Here_Desc: Unbridled rage is increasing damage dealt. Standing too far away will provoke an attack.
FATEs_Defense_Birds Up_Desc: If the coffee farmer was not already convinced that jacu birds were the worst birds in Tural, he is now, as a hungry flock has swooped down to snack on his precious crop. Repel the feathered fiends and see that the beans survive another day.
FATEs_Defense_Lay Off the Horns_Desc: It's horn-honing season, and the gazelles have set their sights on the ancient stonework at the Shades of Grief. Less enthusiastic about the prospect is a Yok Huy vigilkeeper, who would like you to dissuade the beasts by whatever means necessary.
FATEs_Notorious monster_A Valiant Duel_D: Hearing the anguished cries of his brethren, Vorjirzur the Valiant has stepped forth to avenge them. Prove your mettle and bring this lauded warrior of the Chirwagur to his knees.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Big Storm Coming: As the Yok Huy histories tell it, the dread serpent Durzurgir slithers across raging tempests, wreaking havoc upon the land as the wind dies down. Only the noblest warriors can contend with the so-called Stormrider and live to tell the tale.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Fire Suppression: Enkindled by Valigarmanda's calamitous flames, the fearsome Racaqurq has descended the mountain in search of a worthy warrior. Until the stoutstrider returns with reinforcements, you are the only thing standing between Wachunpelo and destruction.
FATEs_Notorious monster_Panaq Attack_Des: Legend has it that a great winged creature haunts Panaqpelu Retreat, lurking in the shadows until it is ready to feast. The Pelu eater prefers its prey fresh from the hot springs, and its next meal has just been served.
FATEs_Slay enemies_By Your Powers Combin: A morbol infestation threatens to spoil the sacred waters of Karvarhur the First. Defend the lake and rout the foul beasts before any lasting damage can be done.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Claws and Effect_Desc: Though it remains unclear how so many bigclaws scuttled into such a small reservoir, one thing is certain: they cannot be suffered to disrupt the natural ecosystem.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Gust Stop Already_Des: Agitated wind sprites have stormed into Proof, whipping up fierce gales that threaten to erode the gravestones. Take up arms and calm their fury, that the Yok Huy might mourn in peace once more.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Megamaguey Mayhem_Des: Many a megamaguey long for the rich, fertile soil of the agave fields─including this pack of particularly pungent ones. Dispatch the creatures before they have the chance to lay roots.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Pasture Expiration Da: A freshly hatched urqocampa possesses an appetite greater than a hungry household of Pelupelu─so one can easily imagine what an entire swarm of them will do to the alpacas' grazing plain if they are not swiftly dealt with.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Ratels So Ravenous_De: Driven to desperation by hunger pangs, a clan of ratels has begun to encroach upon Wachunpelo. Stave them off before they discover a taste for alpacas...or worse.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Salty Showdown_Desc: A cadre of Chirwagur has stationed themselves outside the saltern, harassing any who approach. They can be convinced to retreat by way of force, provided someone rises to the challenge.
FATEs_Slay enemies_So Long, Suckers_Desc: In Urqopacha, few creatures are feared more than the bloodsuckers─ruthless predators who drain the life from anything they can sink their teeth into. If their numbers are not soon thinned, they are bound to leave a trail of mangled corpses in their wake.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Too Irate to Migrate_: A flock of zu has swooped down to forage near the road to Wachunpelo. These short-tempered fowl must be dealt with swiftly, lest they pose a threat to passing civilians.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Weeding the Garden_De: To ensure a high-quality mate crop, neither pest nor weed is welcome in the vicinity of Miplu's Mate Garden. Invasive ochus are no exception, and the farmers require capable cullers to exterminate the stinking seedkin.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Wolf Parade_Desc: Some Pelupelu claim that a full supply wagon is the key to a full coinpurse. Others argue that it is an invitation for unwanted guests on the road, as this idle caravan has just discovered.
FATEs_Slay enemies_Young Volcanoes_Desc: The flames of Naryor Gorna have birthed a bevy of baby bombs who are eager to put their explosive abilities to the test. Douse their fiery aspirations before the volcanic winds carry them to Worlar's Echo.
Fateevent_684_Text: Oh gods, no! There's too many of them! And they're coming for our coffee beans!
Fateevent_686_Text: I feared as much... It seems the recent storm has agitated the wind sprites.
Npcyell_16716_Text: Sorry, I'll get out of your way!
Npcyell_16718_Text: If the glyphs are lost, our ancestors will die!
Npcyell_16721_Text: Excellent work. The wind sprites have settled.
Npcyell_16722_Text: Thanks to you, the glyphs are undamaged.
Npcyell_16723_Text: Now we need but hope the Stormrider won't show itself.
Npcyell_16724_Text: It appears I spoke too soon! Save yourself, outsider!
Npcyell_16800_Text: Shoo! That's my harvest, you feathered freaks!
